# Core Engine Instruction Maps - Comprehensive Overview

This overview provides a complete guide to all available instruction maps for composing core_engine components into different institutional-grade trading and analytics systems using the enhanced 10 Core Architecture Rules.

## Available Instruction Maps

### 1. [Institutional Backtest Workflow](mdc:.cursor/rules/institutional-backtest-workflow.mdc)
**Purpose**: Historical simulation and strategy validation
**Key Components**: DataManager, RegimeEngine, RiskManager, BacktestEngine, PortfolioAnalytics
**Use Cases**: Strategy development, historical analysis, performance validation
**Complexity**: Medium
**Timeline**: Hours to days

### 2. [Live Trading Desk Orchestration](mdc:.cursor/rules/live-trading-desk-orchestration.mdc)
**Purpose**: Real-time institutional trading operations
**Key Components**: LiveDataManager, RealTimeRiskManager, ExecutionEngine, LivePortfolioManager
**Use Cases**: Production trading, real-time execution, automated trading
**Complexity**: High
**Timeline**: Continuous operation

### 3. [Regime Analyzer Configuration](mdc:.cursor/rules/regime-analyzer-configuration.mdc)
